# Push Changes to GitHub

After completing implementation work in this project:

1. Commit changes with a clear, accurate message following existing repo style.
2. Push to `origin/main` (or the current working branch) unless the user explicitly says not to push.
3. Do not push secrets (`.env`, credentials, tokens).
4. If GitHub auth fails, set up credentials and retry, or give the user exact steps to finish the push.

The remote repository is `https://github.com/moonnotice7/web-dev-port`.
